Story 12: Predict Page - COMPLETED

## Implementation Summary

Created the main prediction page at `/predict` that integrates all prediction components into a functional interface.

## Files Created

1. `src/app/predict/page.tsx` - Server Component with authentication check
2. `src/app/predict/predict-page-client.tsx` - Client Component with prediction logic

## Key Features Implemented

✅ Page is protected (requires authentication)
✅ Redirects to login if not authenticated with return URL
✅ Displays TweetInput component with character counter
✅ Shows UsageIndicator with remaining predictions
✅ "Analyze" button triggers prediction API call
✅ Button is disabled while loading or at usage limit
✅ Displays PredictionResult after successful prediction
✅ Handles and displays API errors appropriately (401, 429, 500)
✅ Works in both light and dark mode (uses shadcn/ui tokens)
✅ Is mobile responsive (responsive container and card layout)

## Implementation Details

### Server Component (page.tsx)
- Uses BetterAuth to check session
- Redirects to login with redirect query parameter if not authenticated
- Passes user info to client component

### Client Component (predict-page-client.tsx)
- Manages state: tweetText, isAnalyzing, prediction, error, usageData
- Integrates TweetInput for post entry
- Shows UsageIndicator at top with user welcome message
- Analyze button calls /api/predict with proper error handling
- Disables analyze button when:
  - Already analyzing
  - Text is empty
  - Text exceeds 280 characters
  - Daily limit reached (remainingToday === 0)
- Handles API responses:
  - Success: displays prediction via PredictionResult
  - Error: shows error message via PredictionResult
  - 429: daily limit exceeded
  - 401: authentication required
- Refreshes usage indicator after successful prediction
- Reset functionality clears form and results

### Responsive Design
- Container with max-w-4xl for optimal reading width
- Responsive padding and spacing
- Mobile-friendly card layouts
- Works in both light and dark modes

## Testing Notes

All acceptance criteria met:
- Authentication protection working
- Redirect to login with return URL
- All components properly integrated
- Loading states handled
- Error states handled
- Usage limits enforced in UI
- Mobile responsive
- Dark mode compatible

Lint and typecheck passed successfully.
